text.tspan: Block (3) - Negates damage from the next physical attack.
Piercing Kick (5) - Deals 2STR + 2INT damage to target enemy. Enemies
in the back or second from the back are targetable and take full damage
ROTC Drill (5) - Increases the stamina of the target ally (not self) by five.
Art of Death (10) - Deals pure damage equal to the amount of health missing
Advice: Jennifer is adept at capitalizing on vulnerabilities in the enemies'
formation. Piercing Kick can deal with glass cannons in the back lines, and
Art of Death ruins tanks who have been left out too long. ROTC Drill is nice,
but Jennifer has problems with stamina herself, so use it sparingly.
Vitalize (2) - Heals all allied units for INT + 5 health.
Invigorate (3) - Adds one stamina to all allied units.
Remove (7) - Removes one status of choice from target allied unit.
Emboss (10) - Increases DEF of all allied units by Jenny's DEF for two turns.
Advice: Jenny might not seem that useful at first, but Vitalize and
Invigorate are very cheap spells (especially with Jenny's excellent speed).
Remove can be used on stunned allies, and Emboss is a powerful tool
against area damage. Jenny is one of the few healers who can function
while incurring Drain, since her spells are so cheap. However, watch out
Duo (Passive) - Presence on the field with Rachel Levenseller increases
SPD by two and makes Morgan immune to Bind.
Dance of Knives (5) - Deals 5 * (STR + 10) damage to target enemy.
Dance of Dazing (5) - Deals 40 pure damage to all enemy units (AoE),
stunning the frontmost one for one turn.
Dance of Death (10) - Only available when Rachel is on the field. Deals
3STR + 50 (AoE) damage to all enemies. Upon cast, Rachel is swapped out.
Advice: Having Rachel on the field makes Morgan immune to Bind.
Aside from that though, Morgan is vulnerable to Stun and Drain. Also,
be prepared to swap Morgan after using Dance of Death; Rachel won't be
present and Morgan will be out of stamina.
Qigong (3) - Increases DEF by 2 for three turns. Duration is refreshed,
extra DEF stacks upon reuse. All extra DEF is lost when the duration expires.
Unrefined Kick (3) - Deals 3STR + 10 damage to target enemy. Natasha
receives damage equal to half the damage dealt. Received damage is fatal.
Gungnir Flourish (8) - Deals 6STR + 30 damage to a target enemy unit.
Gungnir Combo (10) - Deals 8 * (2STR + 10) damage to a target enemy unit.
Advice: Natasha has high health, and Qigong only improves her tanking
power. Gungnir Flourish and Gungnir Combo are some of the most
powerful attacks in the game, though Gungnir Combo relies on the enemy
having low DEF. That being said, Natasha's speed is not great, and she has
no status control, so consider complimenting her with someone who does.
True Strike (5) - Deals 2STR + 2INT damage to target enemy, ignoring DEF.
Phalanx (5) - Increases Ulri's DEF by 10 and inflicts Bind for four turns.
Oblation (10) - Consume 70% of Ulri's maximum health. All allied units
(including Ulri) gain ten stamina. Damage dealt to Ulri is fatal.
Advice: Ulri has impressive defenses. Bind incurred from Phalanx can be
removed (unlike Katherine's), and True Strike is deceptively powerful.
However, Oblation is the true game-changing ability in Ulri's arsenal,
allowing several party members to use 10-cost abilities twice in a short
amount of time. If you have exceptional healing, Oblation can be used
several times, since Ulri herself gains the stamina (a rare mechanic). A
word of caution, though -- Oblation won't work on targets incurring Drain,
so find a way to remove such enemies from the field before using it.
Duo (Passive) - Presence on the field with Morgan Bates increases DEF by
four and makes Rachel immune to Mute.
Dance of Valor (8) - Grants party immunity to Drain for two turns.
Dance of Might (8) - Grants party immunity to Stun for two turns.
Dance of Life (10) - Only available when Morgan is on the field. Heals all
allied units for Rachel's current health. Upon cast, Morgan is swapped out.
Advice: Rachel has impressive stats (especially when Morgan is on the field)
but needs stamina boosters to maintain her skills for long periods. Dance
of Valor and Dance of Might are uniquely powerful, and Dance of Life is
the most powerful heal in the game. Just be careful about Stun or Drain,
depending on the dance you're doing.
